The paper discusses a framework for asynchronous distributed systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses practical Byzantine fault tolerance (pBFT), which is a topic that falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper proposes an alternative framework for distributed ledgers, which is a topic that falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses network optimization and domination relationships, which are topics that fall under the categories of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY), respectively.
